Lecturers from the different Chairs will introduce students in their first semester to the research topics that they are working on or have worked on in the near past. Each meeting will be devoted to discussing a text (or more texts) written by the lecturer themselves or by other relevant authors.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course has the following goals:
- introduce students to methods and concrete examples of ongoing philosophical research in different areas,
- help students understand what areas or questions they would like to pursue further in their specialisation,
- familiarize with current research directions in the department,
- start developing research skills.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On the completion of the subject, the student has received an overview of methods and concrete examples of current research in philosophy, has developed research skills, the capacity for academic engagement and cooperation with fellow students and lecturers.
